i.d: Elasticity is the expected change of stock return variance for a given change in the stock price. It is an attempt to model the often exhibited inverse non-linear relationship between volatility of stock returns and the price of the stock. It is important for measuring warrant values because stocks with a high elasticity will tend to exhibit lower variance of returns as the stock price moves higher, and hence reduce the value of the warrant by decreasing the chance that the stock will move even higher. The original issue variance is the value that is originally reported when the warrant is issued.
